g.text: VAGNER'S SERVER FLOW WHEN NOT USING CACHED DATA
If there are results, cache them
Request every map needed from Google Maps API
At this point, the number of calls made to Google Maps API
depends on how many Tweets were received from the Twitter API.
The following displays the flow to request one single map from
the Google Maps API, and how to process the response. The call
to Google Maps API is in a for each loop to request the proper number of maps.
When all maps are downloaded and cached, serve response html file
The file received has  tags with src attribute
set to server's /mapCache/{map name} directory. The
client browser proceeds to request those resources and
the server serves the specified map resources.The following
illustrates the flow of requesting and getting a map from
There will be a request and a response as above
for each map needed to populate the html response file.
